thread.title: Class 1 District 3 softball tournament information

author: Dave Roberts Staff Writer
title: Class 1 District 3 softball tournament information
text: Class 1 District 3 softball tournament information Crocker has been tabbed as the team to beat in Class 1 District 3's softball tournament Comment   Dave Roberts Posted Oct. 3, 2015 at 1:25 AM By Dave RobertsStaff Writer Posted Oct. 3, 2015 at 1:25 AM Crocker (17-3) has been selected as the top seed for the Missouri Class 1 District 3 Tournament, to be held this coming week at St. Elizabeth. St. Elizabeth (5-13) is seeded No. 2, Newburg No. 3, Tuscumbia (1-17) No. 4 and Stoutland (0-20) No. 5. In first-round action on Wednesday, Oct. 7 Tuscumbia plays Stoutland at 5 p.m. In semifinal games on Thursday, Oct. 8, Crocker faces the Tuscumbia-Stoutland winner at 5 p.m. while St. Elizabeth takes on Newburg at 7 p.m. The district championship game is slated for Friday, Oct. 9. The District 3 champion will play the District 4 champion in Class 1 Sectional action Oct. 14. Schools in District 4 include Clopton, Community, New Haven, Silex, Van-Far and Wellsville. That sectional survivor moves on to state quarterfinal play on Oct. 17. By Dave Roberts   Dave Roberts
